TITLE: AN IOT ENABLED PREDICTIVE SAFETY SYSTEM FOR UNDERGROUND MINES USING MACHINE LEARNING-BASED HAZARD DETECTION

Underground mining is most hazardous activity due to presence of harmful gases. 
This project aims to predict and detect potential hazards in underground mines.
Various sensors such as SO2, CO, NO2 and MPU6050 accelerometer are used to detect toxic gases.
By using IOT sensors & ML models, we can enhance worker safety and prevent accidents.
This project presents an IoT-Enabled Predictive Safety System that combines Internet of Things (IoT) technology and Machine Learning (ML) to continuously monitor underground mine conditions and predict potential hazards before they become critical. 
The system enhances miner safety through real-time environmental monitoring, cloud connectivity, and intelligent hazard detection.
The system is built using an ESP32 microcontroller integrated with multiple sensors to collect environmental data such as methane concentration, carbon monoxide levels, nitrogen dioxide levels, temperature, humidity, and vibration. 
The collected data is transmitted to the cloud for storage and analysis, while machine learning algorithms identify abnormal patterns and generate early warnings.
🎯OBJECTIVES: 
Monitor underground mine conditions in real time.
Detect hazardous gas concentrations.
Monitor temperature, humidity, and vibration levels.
Apply machine learning techniques for hazard prediction.
Generate early warnings and alerts for unsafe conditions.
Enable remote monitoring through cloud connectivity.
Improve worker safety and reduce mining accidents.
