📊 RESULTS:
The developed system successfully monitored environmental parameters and detected hazardous conditions in real time. 
Machine learning-based analysis improved the accuracy of hazard detection and enabled predictive warnings before critical situations occurred.
Cloud integration allowed remote accessibility, while the buzzer and mobile alerts provided immediate notifications to workers and supervisors.
📚 CONCLUSION:
The IoT-Enabled Predictive Safety System provides an intelligent and cost-effective solution for underground mine safety. 
By integrating IoT sensors, cloud computing, and machine learning algorithms, the system enables real-time monitoring, predictive hazard detection, and rapid alert generation. 
This significantly improves worker safety, reduces operational risks, and contributes to the development of smarter and safer mining environments.
